7-58:5.2 The notion of agreement As said in the introduction, negotiation is a process aiming at finding an agreement about some matters .
7-59:By agreement, one means a solution that satisfies to the largest possible extent the preferences of both agents .
7-60:In case there is no such solution, we say that the negotiation fails .
7-61:In what follows, we will discuss the different kinds of solutions that may be reached in a negotiation .
7-62:The first one is the optimal solution .
7-63:An optimal solution is the best offer for both agents .
