9-1:In this section we will present some examples in order to illustrate our general framework .
9-2:Example 7 (No argumentation) .
9-3:Let O = {o1, o2} be the set of all possible offers .
9-4:Let P and C be two agents, equipped with the same theory: A, F, , R, Def such that A = ∅, F(o1) = F(o2) = ∅, = ∅, R = ∅, Def = ∅ .
9-5:In this case, it is clear that the two offers o1 and o2 are nonsupported .
